40
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,640
The first question from Andrey Zubanov.

41
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:08,640
Hello Sergey!

42
00:03:08,740 --> 00:03:13,880
Tell please, what is the optimal voltage that should be supplied to a Tesla transformer?

43
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,500
Below what is it not worth lowering?

44
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:21,640
I mean installation of Akula Kulabukhov type.

45
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,440
Interesting question.

46
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:29,640
Slightly incorrectly formulated.

47
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:38,380
In terms of, you can't here speak about what voltage I can specifically recommend.

48
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,480
Because all systems are different.

49
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:48,300
And they require their minimal investment of spent power.

50
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:54,300
Including, this very strongly depends on system dimensions.

51
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:59,400
Applicable to this installation we're speaking about.

52
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:05,880
There the Tesla transformer works jointly with a so-called antenna.

53
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,800
Desirable to make from aluminum.

54
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:16,280
And inside the antenna a gradient coil with its inductor is additionally placed.

55
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:24,480
This part additionally introduces its changes into the common system's work.

56
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,300
Type of Tesla transformer.

57
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:31,120
Here this antenna for Tesla in this system.

58
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:36,200
It's simultaneously also an isolated capacity.

59
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:49,120
That is, the system that tunes this Tesla transformer in the mode of combining LC resonance with frequency on the length of its conductor.

60
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:56,800
And simultaneously it also serves as a radiating system for the gradient coil.

61
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:01,280
So what can it be?

62
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:04,660
What voltage potential?

63
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:07,500
It needs to be picked individually.

64
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:19,960
This value will compose from what minimal power needs to be applied to the Tesla transformer itself.

65
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:32,480
And plus this power should be enough for the interaction of the antenna with the gradient coil with its inductor.

66
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:43,500
It turns out an interesting situation that this voltage will need to be picked in practice.

67
00:05:43,500 --> 00:06:06,000
Because if we set some minimal time for system trigger — in particular in this installation, looking at my scheme, you can set the duration of the Tesla transformer or controlled Kacher trigger.

68
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:15,560
So, in this time the system should get the necessary portion of energy to reach the operating mode.

69
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:28,100
Naturally, the shorter this time of Tesla transformer work in on-state, the larger voltage amplitude will need to be applied to it.

70
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:40,060
And when working with this system, no interesting effects may arise if this threshold isn't passed.

71
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:49,760
The Tesla transformer in this installation works also in static potential mode on the aluminum antenna.

72
00:06:50,760 --> 00:07:04,620
That is, all these talks that go about unipolar pulse — naturally, they're slightly incorrectly expressed for this system.

73
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:10,760
That is, the moment comes — people try to find a unipolar pulse, and there is none.

74
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:19,920
And impossible to get unipolar there — more precisely, it doesn't look at all like a unipolar pulse.

75
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:31,560
It turns out, this antenna should be charged with static positive potential to a certain voltage rating.

76
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:37,720
This rating threshold for us is 3.73 kV.

77
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:44,600
That is, below the minimum value processes in this system won't go at all.

78
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:48,860
You can indirectly assess this by such parameters.

79
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,100
Does the Tesla transformer work in this mode.

80
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:58,300
Take some capacitor with voltage not lower than 1000 V.

81
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:03,580
Capacity is not strongly important, say half a µF.

82
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:10,700
One plate of this capacitor we connect to the grounding wire of the Tesla transformer.

83
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:15,120
And to the other plate make a metal plate.

84
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:18,740
Approximately 10 by 10 cm in size.

85
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:22,160
And bring it to the antenna.

86
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:29,760
Parallel to the transformer lead mandatorily connect a needle voltmeter.

87
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:38,920
Because testers and others will be subject to high-frequency pickups when the Tesla transformer works.

88
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,800
And will show incorrectly or will fail.

89
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:49,020
Any needle device will suit us with voltage not lower than 300 V.

90
00:08:50,080 --> 00:09:02,800
And it turns out, when we start the Tesla transformer, without any diodes, on the capacitor there's a constant voltage present.

91
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:12,440
At that, this metal plate is located at a distance of approximately 5-10 cm from the antenna.

92
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:16,220
Which is located at the hot end of the Tesla transformer.

93
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:25,500
If we see constant voltage shown by our device, then it means Tesla is in the correct mode.

94
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:28,000
Question number 2, also from Andrey.

95
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:34,660
By your description I calculated a coil on Gorchilin's website.

96
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,140
The wire seemingly was good.

97
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:44,300
At check on the tube in one layer the turn count and height matched the calculation.

98
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:46,480
Wire length 50 m.

99
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:49,260
But the inductance turned out higher.

100
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:51,620
Here he cites the inductance.

101
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:53,420
Here 235 µH.

102
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,820
Should be 208.

103
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,500
Wire yellow-green.

104
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:02,740
Ratings here 4 mm.

105
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:10,020
So the essence of the question is clear.

106
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:17,620
The person for checking program calculations wound this conductor in one layer on the tube.

107
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,660
Completely correctly performed action.

108
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:25,440
I determined that the turn count matched the calculations.

109
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:30,520
Means the parameters were entered into the program correctly.

110
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:32,240
And the inductance didn't match.

111
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:37,840
Inductance may not match for many reasons.

112
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,120
But I don't see a strong difference here.

113
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:43,800
208 and 235 µH.

114
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,000
Quite a small difference.

115
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,200
Reasons may be.

116
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:55,560
The material applied for the conductor.

117
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,280
That is, the copper has impurities.

118
00:10:59,340 --> 00:11:02,200
Or impurities present in the tube itself.

119
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:09,280
Understand that if this was a sewer pipe, it's often made from recycled material.

120
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:12,360
Especially these gray sewer pipes.

121
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,200
And this could increase inductance.

122
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:20,060
This doesn't mean that all is lost here.

123
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:30,180
It turns out the person asks, will these parameters affect wave resonance.

124
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:37,040
Will it be higher and will he need to make Tesla at a higher frequency.

125
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:41,500
The inductance won't affect wave resonance in any way.

126
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:45,680
This parameter relates to LC resonance of the system.

127
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,460
So with this everything is normal here.

128
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:57,220
This will affect how you'll wind the grenade further.

129
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:05,660
That is, you'll have slightly more turns wound counter at subsequent layers.

130
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:10,280
After the second layer of winding this coil.

131
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,520
Well, and that's all.

132
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:16,660
By this you'll be able to bring the coil to an optimal mode.

133
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:20,200
There's still one more moment.

134
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:39,740
The bigger the conductor length and the thinner the conductor we'll wind this system with, the larger turn count we naturally get and the coil dimensions may change.

135
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:51,060
That is, you need to understand the longer the coil, the more by length the overlap of winding layers on each other goes.

136
00:12:51,880 --> 00:13:00,840
And each layer, its length, the program calculates for us under a single-layer coil.

137
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,840
And we wind it multi-layer.

138
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:17,440
And so each this layer additionally introduces into calculations an error of such format that increases interlayer capacity.

139
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:20,300
This moment will also need to be considered.

140
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:33,720
Since interlayer capacity increased and we already can't fix it in any way — winding a multi-layer coil — this parameter can be leveled by reducing inductance.

141
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:51,800
That is, you need not specifically clearly orient on the inductance the calculations showed, but make this inductance smaller in practice, compensating the coil's interlayer capacity.

142
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:54,060
And it turns out too.

143
00:13:55,800 --> 00:14:05,980
It turns out that the frequency of wave processes will be equal exactly to wire length.

144
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:16,380
All other moments we can smooth by changing turn count — that is, change coil inductance.

145
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:17,800
Question number 3.

146
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:27,180
On the scheme on the resonator and inductor winding you write that the inductor should be 4 times shorter than the resonator.

147
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:31,520
And you most likely experimented with different ratios.

148
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:44,540
Vorobyov in one of the videos calculated that it's desirable to make the inductor length 3 times less relative to, I understand, the resonator length.

149
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:47,040
That's the most stable.

150
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:52,660
You can, yes, try to work at different lengths.

151
00:14:53,380 --> 00:15:00,780
I work at lengths when my inductor is a quarter of the resonator length.

152
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,740
This relates to the grenade.

153
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,540
Or half.

154
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,600
Three times I didn't make.

155
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:11,320
Here we're guided by what rules.

156
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:14,060
This is the rule of length ratio.

157
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:22,320
This means how much time the wave will impact on your resonator.

158
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:29,780
Here the binding goes of impact time to conductor length.

159
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:35,500
The wave physically moves along the wire and exerts its impact.

160
00:15:35,580 --> 00:15:39,400
This impact is taken by the grenade conductor for us.

161
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:51,680
So if you need to constructively reduce the time of this impact, you reduce the length of your inductor too.

162
00:15:52,720 --> 00:16:02,140
But the thing is, here there's still such a moment — our inductor is in LC resonance.

163
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:21,160
And mandatorily we need to consider the fact that the frequency of this LC resonance should be a multiple of some wave processes frequency exactly in the grenade.

164
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:35,540
That is, those who have spectrum analyzer devices, those people can quite easily examine these moments of dependency.

165
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,540
How is this done?

166
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:40,080
Connect the spectrum analyzer to the grenade.

167
00:16:40,380 --> 00:16:46,960
And to it from the lab signal generator apply various frequencies.

168
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:58,040
And look by signal amplitude on the spectrum analyzer, what frequency is better for us to choose, what to stop at.

169
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:18,340
If you do this measurement on the oscilloscope in FFT mode — so-called fast Fourier transform — this isn't completely the same as conducting measurement on a spectrum analyzer.

170
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:25,460
The thing is, FFT mode in an oscilloscope is a math function.

171
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:40,460
It takes a reference for its calculations from the signal that comes to the oscilloscope input and already by math way decomposes its harmonic range.

172
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:45,320
This is if in general features, not going strongly into details.

173
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:59,720
So what an oscilloscope can show specifically in FFT mode doesn't always correspond to what will be in practice.

174
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:10,120
Because it'll show a math range, but what'll be by fact the oscilloscope doesn't fix.

175
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:24,540
Because a math function in no way can compare to the capabilities of a spectrum analyzer that looks at what happens in reality in your coil.

176
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:37,620
A spectrum analyzer is arranged differently — it has an analog input and only then goes processing, for example, in digital format, if it's new types of devices.

177
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:41,220
And here is a math function.

178
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:50,720
So it'll show you in this mode exactly the reference frequencies at which these moments can be.

179
00:18:51,060 --> 00:18:54,060
And all these frequencies will need to be checked in practice.

180
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,380
Here is the difficulty.

181
00:18:57,380 --> 00:19:09,280
And this inductor length can be well picked specifically in practice if you have specifically a spectrum analyzer.

182
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:29,360
That is, find on the spectrum analyzer screen the biggest spectral peak expressed in dBm — this value from decibel maximum.

183
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:32,460
And change the inductor length.

184
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:42,640
And look does the amplitude of this signal increase — height in dBm — or decrease.

185
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:47,260
So this can be tuned having such a device.

186
00:19:47,260 --> 00:20:00,720
Well, if there's no such possibility and no one to turn to, then you'll need to build in practice, look — which significantly complicates tuning.

187
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:17,160
I'd recommend nevertheless adhering to clear multiples, because the inductor length and resonator length are divided by whole numbers exactly by lengths.

188
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:26,960
Because the grenade — this gradient coil — it's also a high-frequency Tesla transformer.

189
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:30,000
And is made by the same rules.

190
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:36,420
The only thing — here we have additional counter windings.

191
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:47,240
And it turns out we can make these systems with these same effects on Tesla transformers.

192
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:57,650
Simply, a Tesla transformer at high frequencies will be very small by its dimensions and will already work ineffectively.

193
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:05,620
So such a winding of grenade-type coil was invented.

194
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:17,180
Also don't forget that into the length of the inductor wound over the grenade enter all the lengths of connecting wires going to the inductor.

195
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:20,560
Turns wound on ferrite.

196
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:30,680
That is, all these additional conductor lengths determine the total system length.

197
00:21:31,340 --> 00:21:41,780
And the tuning principle is the same as in a Tesla transformer in powerful systems, when we have an inductor on the Tesla transformer.

198
00:21:41,780 --> 00:21:56,360
And part of its conductor — on it there's a movable contact that we, moving along the inductor, do maximum matching by its lengths.

199
00:21:56,820 --> 00:22:06,120
In a Tesla transformer this is easier to do, and at us in this case here the conductor is in insulation.

200
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:13,900
So I recommend nevertheless adhering to clear multiples of length.

201
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:21,120
This is a quarter and half of the length from the length of the resonator conductor.

202
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:24,380
The fourth question from Andrey.

203
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:28,360
Is there interaction of the resonator with its inductor?

204
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:35,160
That is, at a short of one of them, should the inductance of the other change?

205
00:22:35,980 --> 00:22:44,980
Yes, naturally, at a short circuit of one of coupled coils, the inductance of the other will change.

206
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:55,360
But since the system at us is wound without a core, the change of this inductance won't be too critical.

207
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:59,740
So that frequencies strongly went away with us.

208
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:07,700
And again, this phenomenon will affect only the parameters of LC resonance.

209
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:13,860
With wave processes on conductor length all will also be stable.

210
00:23:15,660 --> 00:23:23,400
You can conduct these experiments independently if you have an inductance meter.

211
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:28,400
Well, and now on one of the grenades I'll demonstrate this effect.

212
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:30,580
How much the inductance will go away.

213
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,940
Now you see the inductor inductance.

214
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:38,680
The device is connected to it.

215
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:43,840
And here are two leads directly from the grenade.

216
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:46,360
Now I do the shorting.

217
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:54,580
And see that the inductance for us changes insignificantly.

218
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:08,070
That is, not having a core inside, the system is subjected to not too strong detuning.
